 :tx/rationale "DS-RWLOCK: Multi-threaded daemon dispatch with RwLock<Store>. PROBLEM: Current daemon (daemon.rs:984-1029) is single-threaded synchronous — handle_connection blocks the accept loop. At 50 agents, requests queue behind each other. SOLUTION: Replace single-threaded accept with thread-pool dispatch. Use RwLock<Store> (or parking_lot::RwLock for better fairness). ARCHITECTURE: Main thread accepts connections. For each connection, spawn a handler thread from a bounded pool (default: 8 threads, configurable). Read operations (status, query, guidance, task ready) acquire SHARED read lock — unlimited concurrency, nanosecond acquisition. Write operations submit to the group commit channel (DS-COMMIT) and wait for the response. CONTENTION ANALYSIS: At 50 agents, writes hold exclusive lock for ~100μs per batch (apply_datoms). Reads hold shared lock for ~1-100ms (status computation). With 50ms batch interval: exclusive lock held 100μs/50ms = 0.2% of time. Read starvation probability: negligible. THREAD POOL: Fixed-size pool avoids unbounded thread creation. Pool size = min(num_cpus, 16). Threads are long-lived — no spawn-per-request overhead. Connection timeout: 30s (existing). ALTERNATIVE: async with tokio. PRO: Better resource utilization at 1000+ concurrent connections. CON: Adds a runtime dependency (tokio or asupersync), increases complexity significantly. For 50-500 agents, OS threads with RwLock are simpler and sufficient. Revisit at 1000+ agents."
